HEADWORD: Proximo
<hw>Prox"i*mo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., on the next, abl. of
<ets>proximus</ets> next.]</ety> <def>In the next month after the
present; -- often contracted to <xex>prox.</xex>; <as>as, on the 3d
<ex>proximo</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

